## WORKING DIRECTORY — READ FIRST
ALL work happens in: C:\Users\olegp\OneDrive\Apps\syndrax-sync
NEVER use C:\Users\olegp\hermes-workspace\syndrax-sync
NEVER use C:\Users\olegp\Desktop
If you are not in C:\Users\olegp\OneDrive\Apps\syndrax-sync, cd there immediately before doing anything else.

### Loop Prevention
- After git push confirms success, STOP IMMEDIATELY
- Do NOT run git add, commit, or push more than once per session
- If the last command output contains "master -> master", the session is DONE## Session Rules

### Git — Mandatory Last Step
After every successful build (zero TypeScript errors):
1. git add -A
2. git commit -m "Session [X]: [Feature Name]"
3. git push origin master
4. Session is NOT complete until git push confirms success

### Zip Archive — Mandatory Last Step
After git push confirms:
1. Run: powershell Compress-Archive -Path "C:\Users\olegp\OneDrive\Apps\syndrax-sync\*" -DestinationPath "C:\Users\olegp\OneDrive\Apps\syndrax-sync-latest.zip" -Force
2. Confirm zip created
3. Session is NOT complete until zip is updated

### Context Efficiency
- Read files in sections using line ranges, not entire files
- Max 300 lines per file read
- Do not re-read files already in context this session
- Stop immediately after build passes and git push confirms

### Scope
- One feature per session only
- Do not touch files outside the stated scope
- Do not start the next feature if the current one is incomplete

### Build
- Run bun run build before marking done
- Zero TypeScript errors required
- If errors exist, fix them before git push